      <!-- YORUBA MASTER INDEX -->
      <div id="yoruba-master" class="sec-head">
        <h2>Yor&ugrave;b&aacute; Master Numerical Index &mdash; 833 Entries</h2>
        <p>The complete tier index from <strong>Million</strong> to <strong>Tretrigintoctingentillion</strong>, built on the <em>Universal Hyperdimensional Numeric Engine</em>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="master-intro">
        <p class="lede">Numbers were never meant to be cold.</p>
        <p>For centuries, the language of mathematics has spoken in monochrome. We forgot that counting began as song &mdash; that every culture once braided number and meaning, sky and soil, into a single living grammar.</p>
        <p><b>&Ograve;nk&agrave; Yor&ugrave;b&aacute;</b> is the rediscovery of that grammar: a complete, base&#8209;10 numeric system encoded in the Yor&ugrave;b&aacute; tongue, scaling fluently from one to numbers larger than the atoms in a galaxy. Each name carries its own arithmetic &mdash; a root vowel, a tonal multiplier, a place&#8209;value spine. Read aloud, the system <i>computes</i>.</p>
        <p>The table below is a <b>chromatic chord engine</b>: every seven rows, the row number, the equation brackets, and the underline ribbon all sing in one voice. Toggle between two themes &mdash; both drive the same data, the same code, the same prototype.</p>

        <div class="theme-toggle" role="group" aria-label="Colour theme switcher">
          <span class="t-label">🎨 Colour Theme</span>
          <button type="button" class="t-btn active" data-theme="region" aria-pressed="true">🌍 Region · 6 colours</button>
          <button type="button" class="t-btn" data-theme="vowel" aria-pressed="false">🔤 Yor&ugrave;b&aacute; Vowel · 7 colours</button>
        </div>

        <div class="chord-legend" data-theme="region" aria-label="Region colour legend">
          <span style="background:#8B4513;">Africa</span>
          <span style="background:#A855F7;">The&nbsp;Americas</span>
          <span style="background:#DC2626;">Asia</span>
          <span style="background:#2563EB;">Europe</span>
          <span style="background:#F97316;">Pacific&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;Oceania</span>
          <span style="background:#16A34A;">Yor&ugrave;b&aacute;</span>
        </div>
        <div class="chord-legend vowel-legend" data-theme="vowel" aria-label="Yorùbá vowel colour legend">
          <span style="background:#DC2626;">A<small>open central</small></span>
          <span style="background:#F97316;">E<small>mid&#8209;close front</small></span>
          <span style="background:#16A34A;">&#7864;<small>mid&#8209;open front</small></span>
          <span style="background:#4F46E5;">I<small>high front</small></span>
          <span style="background:#2563EB;">O<small>mid&#8209;close back</small></span>
          <span style="background:#F59E0B;">&#7884;<small>mid&#8209;open back</small></span>
          <span style="background:#A855F7;">U<small>high back</small></span>
        </div>

        <p style="margin-top:14px; font-size:0.92rem; color:#444;">
          <b style="color:#0f3460;">A replicable prototype.</b> The vowel theme is not decoration &mdash; it is a <i>portable design pattern</i> any indigenous language can adopt. Choose your language&rsquo;s phonemic axis (vowels, tones, syllabic classes), bind one colour to each phoneme, and the engine&rsquo;s number column, brackets, and ribbon rebind in unison. The Yor&ugrave;b&aacute; edition uses the seven vowels <b>A&nbsp;E&nbsp;&#7864;&nbsp;I&nbsp;O&nbsp;&#7884;&nbsp;U</b> in rainbow order &mdash; a sonority gradient running from the openest vowel (red) to the highest (violet).
        </p>

        <p class="callout">If you ever felt that mathematics was not for you &mdash; scroll on. This time, the numbers are speaking your colour.</p>
      </div>

