      <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
      <div class="sec-head">
        <h2>How Any Indigenous Language Plugs In</h2>
        <p>Every language onboards to the Numeric Engine through four standardized layers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="method-grid">
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>1. Expressive Layer</h4>
          <p>The language&rsquo;s own words for numbers &mdash; the living, spoken tier of human communication.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>2. Agbára Layer</h4>
          <p>Exponential notation &mdash; <code>Base &middot; (base<sup>unit</sup>)<sup>exponent</sup></code> &mdash; the computational skeleton.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>3. G-Pulse Layer</h4>
          <p>The 1:3 ratio engine that connects language-native words to powers of ten across planetary scales.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="method-card">
          <h4>4. Hyper&sup2; Layer</h4>
          <p>Short-scale tier roots (&Aacute;&emacr;&#7865;&#769;, &Aacute;&#7865;&#768;&#7865;&#768;, &hellip;) for direct mathematical interoperability with scientific notation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

